1 AMEND House Committee Substitute for House Bill No. 1871, Page 19, Section 115.453, Line
2 53, by inserting after all of said section and line the following:
3
4 "115.646. No contribution or expenditure of public funds shall be made directly by any
5 officer, employee, or agent of any political subdivision, [including school districts and charter
6 schools] special district, or charter school to advocate, support, or oppose the passage or defeat
7 of any ballot measure or the nomination or election of any candidate for public office, or to
8 direct any public funds to, or pay any debts or obligations of, any committee supporting or
9 opposing such ballot measures or candidates. This section shall not be construed to prohibit any
10 public official of a political subdivision, including school districts and charter schools, from
11 making public appearances or from issuing press releases concerning any such ballot measure.
12 Any purposeful violation of this section shall be punished as a class four election offense."; and
13
14 Further amend said bill by amending the title, enacting clause, and intersectional references
15 accordingly.
